Node.Notes: Some change the text (with support from ancient translations) to something like "a wise man is mightier than a strong man." Text means something like "a wise man has great power."
Some change vocalization of text to yield something like "a man of knowledge is [mightier] than a mighty man of strength." Text has "a man of knowledge increases strength."
Most understand this as an unusual spelling for "heights," with sense that wisdoms (wise sayings?) is beyond the understanding of fools.
Repeat of related CAR root ("trouble") from previous word. May be sense of small (from "narrow") here.
Uncertain. Tree assumes dislocated np clause and oath formula: As for ones staggering to the slaughter, if you hold [them] back …
Literally, "it is evil," but in sense of disapproval of what is wrong.
Uncertain "those who change" in what sense. Many take to be change in sense of rebelling against God's authority (hence rebels).
Kisses either as a sign of true friendship or of love/affection.
Sense seems to be to prepare basic necessities of life (here agricultural preparation of field and planting) before building a home/family
